  <h1>Poor Images: Visual Bonds</h1>
  <p1> How is materiality manifested in poor images?</p1>
  <p2>How poor images are distributed and relegated are a direct result of their resolution, a physical property. Even their name is a result of their materiality. </p2>
What is the political value of the poor image?
Democratizing art via bootlegs, allowing audience members to become producers in their own right. (Pro-sumers). Creating visual bonds amongst the working class via memes. Poor images are the “language of the people”.
What is the relationship of speed or velocity and digital images?
The higher the circulation/speed, typically the lower the quality of digital imagery.
